        <methods>
            <methodStep>
                <description>
                    <section>
                        <title>Acoustic Sampling at Cumberland Plain SuperSite</title>
                        <para>A Wildlife Acoustics Songmeter SM3+ acoustic sensor ("CBLP Cumberland Plain 1")  was configured to record continuously at 22,050 Hz in WAV format. The sensor were powered using external solar power and 12v deep cycle batteries. The acoustic sensor is configured to record for 12 hours per day (6 hours around dawn and 6 hours around dusk). The acoustic sensor adjusts itself to record at the correct time (relative to sunset and sunrise) throughout the year using the GPS coordinates of the site.</para>
                    </section>
                </description>
                <instrumentation>Songmeter SM3+ sensor</instrumentation>
            </methodStep>
        </methods>
